    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a4fd15c0_977a8648",
        "filename": "res/imp/date-time-picker-sk.html",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-27T19:03:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My immediate use case for this is to data-bind the value with url-param-sk, in which case it is optionally set on page load and subsequently only modified when the user changes the datetime inside the date-time-picker-sk.  So for me, right now, no observer is needed since I expect the value to only be changed by _updateValue.  I guess in the future there might be other use cases, although I can\u0027t think of one in which we\u0027d have a different element writing the value, other than at page load.",
      "parentUuid": "900e48a9_70ae4360",
